1. Docker Commands 
  for installing the docker on machine  
  sudo yum install docker -y  
    
  for starting the docker service  
  sudo systemctl start docker

  for enabling the docker service (Not necessary its only for the os configuration )
  sudo systemctl enable docker

2. Terraform Commands
   for installing the yum-utils package
   sudo yum install -y yum-utils    

   for official HashiCorp repository (helps to install the latest Terraform version)
   sudo yum-config-manager --add-repo https://rpm.releases.hashicorp.com/AmazonLinux/hashicorp.repo

   for installing the docker on machine  
   sudo yum -y install terraform

3. Installing awscli   (for the latest version of awscli v2 )
   curl "https://awscli.amazonaws.com/awscli-exe-linux-x86_64.zip" -o "awscliv2.zip"
   unzip awscliv2.zip
   sudo ./aws/install

4. Configure AWS CLI
   aws configure   ( Entering the access key, secret key and region after the installing the AWS CLI )

5. Creating the ECR Repository
   used for creating the ECR Repository
   aws ecr create-repository --repository-name fargate-app 

6. Authenticate Docker with ECR
   aws ecr get-login-password --region ap-south-1 | docker login --username AWS --password-stdin 970547365086.dkr.ecr.ap-south-1.amazonaws.com
  
7. Build & Push Image
  docker build -t fargate-app
  docker tag fargate-app:latest 970547365086.dkr.ecr.ap-south-1.amazonaws.com/fargate-app:latest
  docker push 970547365086.dkr.ecr.ap-south-1.amazonaws.com/fargate-app:latest

  
